Defendant Kenneth T Lewis in court with attorney Eric M. Hailstock.  Defendant Kenneth T Lewis in custody.  Megan Marie Williamson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Parties have reached a settlement in this case.  Plea hearing proceeds. Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms or body armor.    Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility. 

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by:  Kenya L. and Jacquelin W.  The Court imposed the following sentence:   
The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 10 years consecutive to any other sentence.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 5 years.  Defendant shall serve 5 years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 
 * DNA sample ordered in 15CF395.
 * Court ordered defendant to pay the DNA surcharge, plus costs and disbursements from monies to be taken by the Department of Corrections from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balances to be paid while on Extended Supervision.
 * Court ordered defendant to have no contact with any gangs or be involved in gang activity.
 * Court ordered defendant to have no contact with Marquis L., Takeyra J. or Tiora W. either directly or by third parties.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - Continued no contact with Marquis L., Takeyra J. or Tiora W. personally or by third party contact;
 - No gang involvement or activity;
 - Undergo a mental health evaluation; follow any treatment recommended;
 - No controlled substances other than those legally prescribed for defendant by a duly licensed physician;
 - No alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - Obtain GED;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Court ordered defendant to pay any balances remaining of the DNA surcharge, costs, surcharges and disbursements.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

Court ordered defendant remanded.

Filed,
Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement;
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
